  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis power-law model used herein is benchmarked against the methodology described in Fraser et al. (2024), as cited via referencesIdentifier, which consolidates best-practice guidance on erythrocyte damage quantification in rotary blood pumps. That reference underpins the choice of the relative hemolysis index (RH) acceptance criterion and the shear-exposure integration approach adopted across all five flow-speed operating points.",
